rComments: Pros: Outgoing professor, really knows his material, good lecturer; not boring.  Gotta love his enthusiasm for math. Cons: Exams are difficult; Doing homework for this class is not enough, you gotta go above and beyond. Did not curve exams, but curved in the end for final grades.  Though I wasn't happy with my exams scores, I pulled off a good grad

The problems on the exams are pretty much taken straight from the examples in class or the homework so I really don't see how people could find his exams hard.  They normally aren't curved because they don't need to be.  It isn't like Carty's class where half the people get less than 50%, and unlike Carty's class he only focuses on what's important
he is sometimes unprepared for class, seems kinda cocky, his exams are terrible! they're so hard and confusing. makes too many mistakes during lecture

Extremely disorganized, offensive, not funny, notes are impossible to keep up with, messes something up on every exam. He knows his stuff but he is a poor instructor. Avoid this professor unless you are very talented at mathematics. Other than that, tests are very unfair, he doesn't prepare his class for the exams he writes. Avoid.
Gets confusing towards the last topic. Really good otherwise.
Do not take his class for his exam is ridiculously hard...... No curve... I would rather recommend Carty....this class is only going to bring your GPA down
COOL. GOOD LECTURES. HARD TEST. NO CURVE. QED
Nice professor, but exams are hard and absolutely no curves.
The teacher's ok, but his curve (or lack of) can be harsh as I found out. He said he wanted the average to be about 75, but it was 70 and still no curve =( This class is gonna pull my gpa down

He was a great professor. His lectures were interesting and really clear. He kept everyone awake for it being a 1.5 hr lecture. His tests could be tricky, but he is fair in he is clear in his expectations. He is also helpful in office hours. I would take another class taught by him.

GO TO CLASS! People who gave him a bad review must not have gone to class or done the homework because Hal is exceptional! Tests can be tricky, but also fair (he needs to separate the A's and the B's somehow) and he always gives easier problems so you can get points.  He is funny and knows how to explain. I would take any other class with Hal.

BEST MATH PROFESSOR I HAVE EVER HAD!I have never had any Math professor that is this straight forward. This man is funny, amazing, and very respectable. He is very clear and he doesn't give curves because it was unnecessary since he knew what he was teaching and most of the class passed it. As long as you GO TO CLASS you will be golden!
Dr. Hal is the best!  He's a funny guy and he knows what he's talking about.  If you can, try to get him, you wont regret it.
His lectures are clear, and more often than not, entertaining. He answers questions succinctly.

Hal was AWESOME, so entertaining and energetic! Math 234 is tricky, but not awful. Do the hwk, it really helps with quizzes and exams. I'd never taken math higher than pre-calc, and I still got a C+. I could've done better, but I really slacked off in disc. Anyone willing to do the work can get an A. If you can take this class with Hal, DO IT!

I learned the material but his tests were not fair. Nothing like the practice tests or homework problems and questions made to trick you. My only C+ ever. Easy if you already took calc in hs which was half the class!
he moves a little fast with his lectures but he's very easy on the eyes and pretty adorable.
